THE third term of Parliament ended last Friday, with members of the houses of the National Assembly and National Council of Provinces returning to their homes and constituencies across the country.Starting today and continuing until September 29, MPs are expected to do constituency work before returning to Cape Town next month to begin the fourth term.Its not known when ANC NEC member Nkosazana Dlamini Zuma will be sworn in as an MP, after Nonceba Mhlauli, spokesperson for ANC chief whip Jackson Mthembu earlier confirmed that Dlamini Zuma would be sworn in but said they were waiting for a date from the speaker s office.The New Age was told Dlamini Zuma will replace Pule Mabe, who resigned from Parliament earlier this month. Mabe quit just two months after being deployed as whip in Parliament s finance committee, replacing now Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs Minister Des van Rooyen.news@thenewage.co.za-Dennis Cruywagen